  "prompt": "How can I get rid of a redirecting virus in Chrome and Opera on my Android?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to remove a redirecting virus from Chrome and Opera on Android:\n\n1. Remove suspicious apps\n- Go to Settings > Apps/Application Manager\n- Look for unfamiliar or suspicious apps\n- Uninstall or disable them\n- Pay special attention to recently installed apps\n\n2. Clear browser cache and data\nIn Chrome:\n- Open Chrome\n- Tap \u22ee (three dots)\n- Go to Settings > Privacy and Security\n- Clear browsing data\n- Clear cache and cookies\n\nIn Opera:\n- Open Opera\n- Tap \u22ee (three dots)\n- Go to Settings > Privacy\n- Clear browsing data\n- Clear cache and cookies\n\n3. Reset browser settings\nChrome:\n- Settings > Advanced > Reset and clean up\n- Tap \"Reset settings\"\n\nOpera:\n- Settings > Advanced\n- Tap \"Reset to default settings\"\n\n4. Use antivirus/anti-malware apps\n- Install reputable mobile security apps like:\n  - Malwarebytes\n  - Bitdefender\n  - AVG Antivirus\n- Run a full system scan\n\n5. If issues persist, factory reset your device\n\nPrevention tips:\n- Only download apps from official stores\n- Check app permissions\n- Keep your device and apps updated",
